# Copy this file to:
# .wiki-runtime/hermes/wiki-agent.env
# chmod 600 .wiki-runtime/hermes/wiki-agent.env
#
# Then edit WIKI_AGENT_COMMAND to match the Hermes command installed on this
# machine. In this mode, Hermes starts or connects to the local LLM backend.
#
# Notes:
# - scripts/wiki_agent refuses to read this file if it is group- or
#   world-writable.
# - Only a small allowlist of variables is honored. Anything outside the
#   allowlist is logged as a warning and ignored. Current allowlist:
#   WIKI_AGENT_COMMAND, WIKI_AGENT_WORKDIR, WIKI_RUNTIME, HERMES_HOME,
#   HF_HOME, HF_TOKEN, TRANSFORMERS_CACHE, OLLAMA_HOST, OLLAMA_MODELS,
#   XDG_CACHE_HOME, TMPDIR, CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES.
# - Prefer an absolute path to the Hermes binary. PATH-resolved names are
#   subject to shadowing by anything earlier in PATH.

WIKI_AGENT_COMMAND=/usr/local/bin/hermes-agent run --project /data/repos/pg-wiki
